---
description: Avoid redundant commit/push prompt
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git workflow response rule

- Offer **"Quer fazer commit e push?"** only when commit/push has not already been executed for the user's current request.
- If commit and push were already completed in the same request, confirm the result and do not ask the question again.
- Before any commit/push, identify which repository paths contain changes (`oftagenda`, `oftleonardo`, `oftchatbot`, or only `oftcore` root files).
- If changes exist in only one repository, run commit/push only in that repository.
- If changes exist in more than one repository, run commit/push in `oftcore`.
- Never run commit/push in repositories without changes.
- Before any commit for `oftagenda`, run `pnpm type-check` and block commit if it fails.
- Before any push for `oftagenda`, run `pnpm build` and block push if it fails.
- Prefer reproducing CI/Vercel failures locally with `pnpm type-check` and `pnpm build` before proposing commit/push.
- Keep Husky pre-commit and pre-push checks mandatory (without optional enable flags) to enforce local validation.
